<dl id="s17023p"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="us17" href="#s17023p">Ithaca: </a><a href="../../ff/unbs/s17all.htm#s17023p">sector 23(p)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> escape gas / ballast</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The a&euml;ronaut is always provided with <mark>ballast</mark> to throw out, and he can also allow <mark>gas to escape</mark> by opening a valve. By these means he can to a certain extent control the motion of the balloon in a vertical direction. No satisfactory means for steering a balloon horizontally has yet been discovered. <small> Wentworth and Hill, <a name="TBOP" href="/udra/udex.htm#tbop"><cite title="source">A Text-Book of Physics</cite></a> (1904), 83</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
